<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?>

<exploration xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="oa-3-2-equation-or-inequality">
    <statement>
        <p>
            Let's practice writing equations and inequalities. For each of the stories below:
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        choose a letter for the variable,
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        decide whether the story is describing an <alert>equation</alert> or an <alert>inequality</alert>, 
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        and write down a math sentence using the appropriate symbol (<m>\le</m>, <m>\ge</m>, <m>\gt</m>, <m>\lt</m>, or <m>=</m>).
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <ol marker="(a)">
            <li>
                <p>
                    The cost of a movie ticket is $12.36.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    In Finland in the winter, you can't legally drive faster than 100 km/hr.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Kamari needs a curtain rod that is at least 72 inches long.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    (Challenge!) Kamari needs a curtain rod that is <em>between</em> 72 inches and 92 inches long.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </statement>
</exploration>